cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper is about a web application for visualizing the learning process of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning frameworks such as Tensorflow and Keras, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of occlusion maps and saliency maps, which are techniques for analyzing neural networks, indicating that it could also be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the modular nature of the framework, which could also make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
